Package com.github.joncros.remoteSensors

Class ComponentAdapter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.joncros.remoteSensors.ComponentAdapter
  • public class ComponentAdapter
extends java.lang.Object
    Uses google's Gson to serialize all of the jsensors (@code Component} objects for this machine into JSON.
    Author:
    joncros

    Returns four JSON strings corresponding to each type of Component (cpu, mobo, gpu, disk). Each string can be parsed to obtain an array of javascript objects (corresponding to all of the cpu cores, for example). To deserialize into javascript objects, use $.parseJSON(data.Component) where Component is cpus, mobos, gpus or disks.

    In line with the jsensors data model, each object has the properties name and sensors. sensors is an object with properties temperatures, fans and loads and each property is an array of name:value pairs for the corresponding sensor. An example of a cpus string: 

    cpus	"[{\"name\":\"cpu name\",\"sensors\":{\"temperatures\":[{\"name\":\"Temp Core #1\",\"value\":57.0},
 {\"name\":\"Temp Core #2\",\"value\":60.0}],\"fans\":[],\"loads\":[{\"name\":
 \"Load CPU Core #1\",\"value\":60.68376},{\"name\":\"Load CPU Core #2\",\"value\":64.10257},
 {\"name\":\"Load CPU Total\",\"value\":62.39316},{\"name\":\"Load Memory\",\"value\":85.67255}]}}]"
